title: Bug 109350: Output parameter not displaying in data set dialog
EB: Output parameter should be displayed in the data set dialog. Details: The output parameter is not currently being shown in the edit data set dialog. Steps to reproduce: 1. Call the stored procedure from the Oracle database. 2. Verify that the query result is being stored in the output parameter as an object. 3. Open the query result page. 4. Note that there is no data returned. Actual result: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR: 1. Call the stored procedure from the Oracle database. 2. Check the query result and ensure it is being stored in the output parameter as an object. 3. Open the query result page and observe that no data is returned. 4. Verify that the output parameter is not displayed in the edit data set dialog.
